attributes.name: MACHINE_TARGET_HOST
attributes.documentation: Interacts with the host and not a WOW64 guest

attributes.name: MACHINE_R3000
attributes.documentation: MIPS little-endian, 0x160 big-endian

attributes.name: MACHINE_R10000
attributes.documentation: MIPS little-endian

attributes.name: MACHINE_ALPHA
attributes.documentation: Alpha_AXP

attributes.name: MACHINE_SH3E
attributes.documentation: SH3E little-endian

attributes.name: MACHINE_AXP64
attributes.documentation: AXP64

attributes.name: MACHINE_ALPHA64
attributes.documentation: ALPHA64

attributes.name: MACHINE_TRICORE
attributes.documentation: Infineon

attributes.name: MACHINE_CEF
attributes.documentation: CEF

attributes.name: MACHINE_CEE
attributes.documentation: CEE

attributes.name: HIGH_ENTROPY_VA
attributes.documentation: DllCharacteristics ASLR with 64 bit address space.

attributes.name: DYNAMIC_BASE
attributes.documentation: File can be relocated - also marks the file as ASLR compatible

attributes.name: NX_COMPAT
attributes.documentation: Marks the file as DEP compatible

attributes.name: NO_SEH
attributes.documentation: The file does not contain structured exception handlers, this must be set to use SafeSEH

attributes.name: APPCONTAINER
attributes.documentation: DllCharacteristics Image should execute in an AppContainer.

attributes.name: WDM_DRIVER
attributes.documentation: Marks the file as a Windows Driver Model (WDM) device driver.

attributes.name: GUARD_CF
attributes.documentation: Image supports Control Flow Guard.

attributes.name: TERMINAL_SERVER_AWARE
attributes.documentation: Marks the file as terminal server compatible

attributes.name: RELOCS_STRIPPED
attributes.documentation: Relocation info stripped from file.

attributes.name: EXECUTABLE_IMAGE
attributes.documentation: File is executable (i.e. no unresolved external references).

attributes.name: LINE_NUMS_STRIPPED
attributes.documentation: Line numbers stripped from file.

attributes.name: LOCAL_SYMS_STRIPPED
attributes.documentation: Local symbols stripped from file.

attributes.name: AGGRESIVE_WS_TRIM
attributes.documentation: Aggressively trim working set

attributes.name: LARGE_ADDRESS_AWARE
attributes.documentation: App can handle >2gb addresses

attributes.name: BYTES_REVERSED_LO
attributes.documentation: Bytes of machine word are reversed.

attributes.name: MACHINE_32BIT
attributes.documentation: 32 bit word machine.

attributes.name: DEBUG_STRIPPED
attributes.documentation: Debugging info stripped from file in .DBG file

attributes.name: REMOVABLE_RUN_FROM_SWAP
attributes.documentation: If Image is on removable media, copy and run from the swap file.

attributes.name: NET_RUN_FROM_SWAP
attributes.documentation: If Image is on Net, copy and run from the swap file.

attributes.name: SYSTEM
attributes.documentation: System File.

attributes.name: DLL
attributes.documentation: File is a DLL.

attributes.name: UP_SYSTEM_ONLY
attributes.documentation: File should only be run on a UP machine

attributes.name: BYTES_REVERSED_HI
attributes.documentation: Bytes of machine word are reversed.

attributes.name: IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_EXPORT
attributes.documentation: Data directory for exported functions.

attributes.name: IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_IMPORT
attributes.documentation: Data directory for import directory.

attributes.name: IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_RESOURCE
attributes.documentation: Data directory for resource section.

attributes.name: IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_EXCEPTION
attributes.documentation: Data directory for exception information.

attributes.name: IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_SECURITY
attributes.documentation: This is the raw file offset and length of the image digital signature. If the image has no embedded digital signature, this directory will contain zeros.

attributes.name: IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_BASERELOC
attributes.documentation: Data directory for image relocation table.

attributes.name: IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_DEBUG
attributes.documentation: Data directory for debug information.

attributes.name: IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_TLS
attributes.documentation: Data directory for image thread local storage.

attributes.name: IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_LOAD_CONFIG
attributes.documentation: Data directory for image load configuration.

attributes.name: IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_BOUND_IMPORT
attributes.documentation: Data directory for image bound import table.

attributes.name: IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_IAT
attributes.documentation: Data directory for image Import Address Table.

attributes.name: IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_DELAY_IMPORT
attributes.documentation: Data directory for Delayed Import Table. Structure of the delayed import table is linker-dependent. Microsoft version of delayed imports is described in the souces "delayimp.h" and "delayimp.cpp", which can be found in MS Visual Studio 2008 CRT sources.

attributes.name: IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_COM_DESCRIPTOR
attributes.documentation: Data directory for .NET headers.

attributes.name: IMAGE_NT_OPTIONAL_HDR32_MAGIC
attributes.documentation: The file is an executable image.

attributes.name: IMAGE_NT_OPTIONAL_HDR64_MAGIC
attributes.documentation: The file is an executable image.

attributes.name: IMAGE_ROM_OPTIONAL_HDR_MAGIC
attributes.documentation: The file is a ROM image.

attributes.name: SECTION_NO_PAD
attributes.documentation: The section should not be padded to the next boundary. This flag is obsolete and is replaced by IMAGE_SCN_ALIGN_1BYTES.

attributes.name: SECTION_LNK_OTHER
attributes.documentation: Reserved

attributes.name: SECTION_LNK_INFO
attributes.documentation: The section contains comments or other information. This is valid only for object files.

attributes.name: SECTION_LNK_REMOVE
attributes.documentation: The section will not become part of the image. This is valid only for object files.

attributes.name: SECTION_LNK_COMDAT
attributes.documentation: The section contains COMDAT data. This is valid only for object files.

attributes.name: SECTION_NO_DEFER_SPEC_EXC
attributes.documentation: Reset speculative exceptions handling bits in the TLB entries for this section.

attributes.name: SECTION_MEM_PURGEABLE
attributes.documentation: Reserved

attributes.name: SECTION_MEM_PURGEABLE
attributes.documentation: Reserved

attributes.name: SECTION_MEM_LOCKED
attributes.documentation: Reserved

attributes.name: SECTION_MEM_PRELOAD
attributes.documentation: Reserved

attributes.name: SECTION_ALIGN_1BYTES
attributes.documentation: Align data on a 1-byte boundary. This is valid only for object files.

attributes.name: SECTION_ALIGN_2BYTES
attributes.documentation: Align data on a 2-byte boundary. This is valid only for object files.

attributes.name: SECTION_ALIGN_4BYTES
attributes.documentation: Align data on a 4-byte boundary. This is valid only for object files.

attributes.name: SECTION_ALIGN_8BYTES
attributes.documentation: Align data on a 8-byte boundary. This is valid only for object files.

attributes.name: SECTION_ALIGN_16BYTES
attributes.documentation: Align data on a 16-byte boundary. This is valid only for object files.

attributes.name: SECTION_ALIGN_32BYTES
attributes.documentation: Align data on a 32-byte boundary. This is valid only for object files.

attributes.name: SECTION_ALIGN_64BYTES
attributes.documentation: Align data on a 64-byte boundary. This is valid only for object files.

attributes.name: SECTION_ALIGN_128BYTES
attributes.documentation: Align data on a 128-byte boundary. This is valid only for object files.

attributes.name: SECTION_ALIGN_256BYTES
attributes.documentation: Align data on a 256-byte boundary. This is valid only for object files.

attributes.name: SECTION_ALIGN_512BYTES
attributes.documentation: Align data on a 512-byte boundary. This is valid only for object files.

attributes.name: SECTION_ALIGN_1024BYTES
attributes.documentation: Align data on a 1024-byte boundary. This is valid only for object files.

attributes.name: SECTION_ALIGN_2048BYTES
attributes.documentation: Align data on a 2048-byte boundary. This is valid only for object files.

attributes.name: SECTION_ALIGN_4096BYTES
attributes.documentation: Align data on a 4096-byte boundary. This is valid only for object files.

attributes.name: SECTION_ALIGN_8192BYTES
attributes.documentation: Align data on a 8192-byte boundary. This is valid only for object files.

attributes.name: SECTION_SCALE_INDEX
attributes.documentation: Tls index is scaled

attributes.name: IMAGE_DEBUG_TYPE_UNKNOWN
attributes.documentation: Unknown value, ignored by all tools.

attributes.name: IMAGE_DEBUG_TYPE_COFF
attributes.documentation: COFF debugging information (line numbers, symbol table, and string table). This type of debugging information is also pointed to by fields in the file headers.

attributes.name: IMAGE_DEBUG_TYPE_CODEVIEW
attributes.documentation: CodeView debugging information. The format of the data block is described by the CodeView 4.0 specification.

attributes.name: IMAGE_DEBUG_TYPE_FPO
attributes.documentation: Frame pointer omission (FPO) information. This information tells the debugger how to interpret nonstandard stack frames, which use the EBP register for a purpose other than as a frame pointer.

attributes.name: IMAGE_DEBUG_TYPE_MISC
attributes.documentation: Miscellaneous information.

attributes.name: IMAGE_DEBUG_TYPE_EXCEPTION
attributes.documentation: Exception information.

attributes.name: IMAGE_DEBUG_TYPE_FIXUP
attributes.documentation: Fixup information.

attributes.name: IMAGE_DEBUG_TYPE_BORLAND
attributes.documentation: Borland debugging information.

attributes.name: number_of_sections
attributes.documentation: Number of sections in the PE.

attributes.name: timestamp
attributes.documentation: PE timestamp.

attributes.name: pointer_to_symbol_table
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_FILE_HEADER::PointerToSymbolTable. Used when the PE image has COFF debug info.

attributes.name: number_of_symbols
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_FILE_HEADER::NumberOfSymbols. Used when the PE image has COFF debug info.

attributes.name: size_of_optional_header
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_FILE_HEADER::SizeOfOptionalHeader. This is real size of the optional header and reflects differences between 32-bit and 64-bit optional header and number of data directories.

attributes.name: characteristics
attributes.documentation: Bitmap with PE FileHeader characteristics. Individual characteristics can be inspected by performing a bitwise AND operation with specific constants.

attributes.name: entry_point
attributes.documentation: Entry point raw offset or virtual address depending on whether YARA is scanning a file or process memory respectively. This is equivalent to the deprecated `entrypoint` keyword.

attributes.name: image_base
attributes.documentation: Image base relative virtual address.

attributes.name: number_of_rva_and_sizes
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER::NumberOfRvaAndSizes. This is the number of items in the IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER::DataDirectory array.

attributes.name: version_info
attributes.documentation: Dictionary containing the PE's version information. Typical keys are: Comments, CompanyName, FileDescription, FileVersion, InternalName, LegalCopyright, LegalTrademarks, OriginalFilename, ProductName, ProductVersion. For more information refer to: ```Example: pe.version_info["CompanyName"] contains "Microsoft"```

attributes.name: number_of_version_infos
attributes.documentation: Number of extracted version information records

attributes.name: version_info_list
attributes.documentation: A array of version information records. Each data record contains key and value of the appropriate data record.

attributes.name: key
attributes.documentation: Key of version information record directory.

attributes.name: value
attributes.documentation: Value of version information record directory.

attributes.name: opthdr_magic
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER::Magic.

attributes.name: size_of_code
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER::SizeOfCode. This is the sum of raw data sizes in code sections.

attributes.name: size_of_initialized_data
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER::SizeOfInitializedData.

attributes.name: size_of_uninitialized_data
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER::SizeOfUninitializedData.

attributes.name: base_of_code
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER::BaseOfCode.

attributes.name: base_of_data
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER::BaseOfData. This field only exists in 32-bit PE files.

attributes.name: section_alignment
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER::SectionAlignment. When Windows maps a PE image to memory, all raw sizes (including size of header) are aligned up to this value.

attributes.name: file_alignment
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER::FileAlignment. All raw data sizes of sections in the PE image are aligned to this value.

attributes.name: linker_version
attributes.documentation: An object with two integer attributes, one for each major and minor linker version.

attributes.name: major
attributes.documentation: Major linker version.

attributes.name: minor
attributes.documentation: Minor linker version.

attributes.name: os_version
attributes.documentation: An object with two integer attributes, one for each major and minor OS version.

attributes.name: major
attributes.documentation: Major OS version.

attributes.name: minor
attributes.documentation: Minor OS version.

attributes.name: image_version
attributes.documentation: An object with two integer attributes, one for each major and minor image version.

attributes.name: major
attributes.documentation: Major image version.

attributes.name: minor
attributes.documentation: Minor image version.

attributes.name: subsystem_version
attributes.documentation: An object with two integer attributes, one for each major and minor subsystem version.

attributes.name: major
attributes.documentation: Major subsystem version.

attributes.name: minor
attributes.documentation: Minor subsystem version.

attributes.name: win32_version_value
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER::Win32VersionValue.

attributes.name: size_of_image
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER::SizeOfImage. This is the total virtual size of header and all sections.

attributes.name: size_of_headers
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER::SizeOfHeaders. This is the raw data size of the PE headers including DOS header, file header, optional header and all section headers. When PE is mapped to memory, this value is subject to aligning up to SectionAlignment.

attributes.name: checksum
attributes.documentation: Integer with the "PE checksum" as stored in the OptionalHeader

overloads.documentation: Function that calculates the "PE checksum" ```Example: pe.checksum == pe.calculate_checksum()```

attributes.name: dll_characteristics
attributes.documentation: Bitmap with PE OptionalHeader DllCharacteristics. Do not confuse these flags with the PE FileHeader Characteristics. Individual characteristics can be inspected by performing a bitwise AND operation with specific constants.

attributes.name: dll_name
attributes.documentation: The name of the DLL, if it exists in the export directory.

attributes.name: export_timestamp
attributes.documentation: The timestamp the export data was created.

attributes.name: size_of_stack_reserve
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER::SizeOfStackReserve. This is the default amount of virtual memory that will be reserved for stack.

attributes.name: size_of_stack_commit
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER::SizeOfStackCommit. This is the default amount of virtual memory that will be allocated for stack.

attributes.name: size_of_heap_reserve
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER::SizeOfHeapReserve. This is the default amount of virtual memory that will be reserved for main process heap.

attributes.name: size_of_heap_commit
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER::SizeOfHeapCommit. This is the default amount of virtual memory that will be allocated for main process heap.

attributes.name: loader_flags
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER::LoaderFlags.

attributes.name: data_directories
attributes.documentation: A zero-based array of data directories. Each data directory contains virtual address and length of the appropriate data directory. Example:  ```pe.data_directories[pe.IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_EXPORT].virtual_address != 0``` Each data directory has the following entries:

attributes.name: virtual_address
attributes.documentation: Relative virtual address (RVA) of the PE data directory. If this is zero, then the data directory is missing. Note that for digital signature, this is the file offset, not RVA.

attributes.name: size
attributes.documentation: Size of the PE data directory, in bytes.

attributes.name: sections
attributes.documentation: Individual section characteristics can be inspected using a bitwise AND operation with specific constants. Examples: ```pe.sections[0].name == ".text"```, ```pe.sections[1].characteristics & pe.SECTION_CNT_CODE```

attributes.name: name
attributes.documentation: Section name.

attributes.name: characteristics
attributes.documentation: Section characteristics.

attributes.name: virtual_address
attributes.documentation: Section virtual address.

attributes.name: virtual_size
attributes.documentation: Section virtual size.

attributes.name: raw_data_offset
attributes.documentation: Section raw offset.

attributes.name: raw_data_size
attributes.documentation: Section raw size.

attributes.name: pointer_to_relocations
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_SECTION_HEADER::PointerToRelocations.

attributes.name: pointer_to_line_numbers
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_SECTION_HEADER::PointerToLinenumbers.

attributes.name: number_of_relocations
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_SECTION_HEADER::NumberOfRelocations.

attributes.name: number_of_line_numbers
attributes.documentation: Value of IMAGE_SECTION_HEADER::NumberOfLineNumbers.

attributes.name: overlay
attributes.documentation: A structure containing members offset and size.

attributes.name: offset
attributes.documentation: Overlay section offset.

attributes.name: size
attributes.documentation: Overlay section size.

attributes.name: rich_signature
attributes.documentation: Structure containing information about the PE's rich signature as documented in http://www.ntcore.com/files/richsign.htm.

attributes.name: offset
attributes.documentation: Offset where the rich signature starts. It will be undefined if the file doesn't have a rich signature.

attributes.name: length
attributes.documentation: Length of the rich signature, not including the final 'Rich' marker.

attributes.name: key
attributes.documentation: Key used to encrypt the data with XOR.

attributes.name: raw_data
attributes.documentation: Raw data as it appears in the file.

attributes.name: clear_data
attributes.documentation: Data after being decrypted by XORing it with the key.

attributes.name: version
attributes.documentation: Function returning a sum of count values of all matching version records. Provide the optional toolid argument to only match when both match for one entry. More information can be found here: http://www.ntcore.com/files/richsign.htm Note: Prior to version 3.11.0, this function returns only a boolean value (0 or 1) if the given version and optional toolid is present in an entry. ```Example: pe.rich_signature.version(24215, 261) == 61```

overloads.documentation: Function returning a sum of count values of all matching `version` records.
Function returning a sum of count values of all matching `version` records that also match the specified `toolid`.

attributes.name: toolid
attributes.documentation: Function returning a sum of count values of all matching toolid records. Provide the optional version argument to only match when both match for one entry. More information can be found here: http://www.ntcore.com/files/richsign.htm Note: Prior to version 3.11.0, this function returns only a boolean value (0 or 1) if the given toolid and optional version is present in an entry. ```Example: pe.rich_signature.toolid(170, 40219) >= 99```

overloads.documentation: Function returning the import hash or imphash for the PE. The imphash is a MD5 hash of the PE's import table after some normalization. The imphash for a PE can be also computed with pefile and you can find more information in Mandiant's blog.
Function returning the index into the sections array for the section that has name. name is case sensitive.
Function returning the index into the sections array for the section that has addr. addr can be an offset into the file or a memory address.
Function returning true if the PE exports function_name or false otherwise.
Function returning true if the PE exports ordinal or false otherwise.
Function returning true if the PE exports regular_expression or false otherwise.
Function returning the index into the export_details array where the named function is, undefined otherwise.
Function returning the index into the export_details array where the exported ordinal is, undefined otherwise.
Function returning the first index into the export_details array where the regular expression matches the exported name, undefined otherwise.

attributes.name: export_details
attributes.documentation: Array of structures containing information about the PE's exports.

attributes.name: offset
attributes.documentation: Offset where the exported function starts.

attributes.name: name
attributes.documentation: Name of the exported function. It will be undefined if the function has no name.

attributes.name: forward_name
attributes.documentation: The name of the function where this export forwards to. It will be undefined if the export is not a forwarding export.

attributes.name: ordinal
attributes.documentation: The ordinal of the exported function, after the ordinal base has been applied to it.

overloads.documentation: Function returning true if the PE imports function_name from dll_name, or false otherwise. dll_name is case insensitive.
Function returning true if the PE imports ordinal from dll_name, or false otherwise. dll_name is case insensitive.
Function returning the number of functions from the dll_name, in the PE imports. dll_name is case insensitive.

Function returning the number of functions from the PE imports where a function name matches function_regexp and a DLL name matches dll_regexp. Both dll_regexp and function_regexp are case sensitive unless you use the "/i" modifier in the regexp.
Function returning true if the PE has a resource with the specified locale identifier. Locale identifiers are 16-bit integers.
Function returning true if the PE has a resource with the specified language identifier. Language identifiers are 8-bit integers.
Function returning true if the PE is a DLL.
Function returning true if the PE is 32bits.
Function returning true if the PE is 64bits.

attributes.name: number_of_imports
attributes.documentation: Number of imports in the PE.

attributes.name: number_of_exports
attributes.documentation: Number of exports in the PE.

attributes.name: resource_timestamp
attributes.documentation: Resource timestamp. This is stored as an integer.

attributes.name: resource_version
attributes.documentation: An object with two integer attributes, major and minor versions.

attributes.name: major
attributes.documentation: Major resource version.

attributes.name: minor
attributes.documentation: Minor resource version.

attributes.name: resources
attributes.documentation: A zero-based array of resource objects, one for each resource the PE has. Individual resources can be accessed by using the [] operator.All resources must have a type, id (name), and language specified. They can be either an integer or string, but never both, for any given level. ```Example: pe.resources[0].type == pe.RESOURCE_TYPE_RCDATA``` ```Example: pe.resources[0].name_string == "F\x00I\x00L\x00E\x00```"

attributes.name: offset
attributes.documentation: Offset for the resource data.

attributes.name: length
attributes.documentation: Length of the resource data.

attributes.name: type
attributes.documentation: Type of the resource (integer).

attributes.name: id
attributes.documentation: ID of the resource (integer).

attributes.name: language
attributes.documentation: Language of the resource (integer).

attributes.name: type_string
attributes.documentation: Type of the resource as a string, if specified.

attributes.name: name_string
attributes.documentation: Name of the resource as a string, if specified.

attributes.name: language_string
attributes.documentation: Language of the resource as a string, if specified.

attributes.name: number_of_resources
attributes.documentation: Number of resources in the PE.

attributes.name: pdb_path
attributes.documentation: Path of the PDB file for this PE if present. Example: ```pe.pdb_path == "D:\workspace\2018_R9_RelBld	arget\checkout\custprof\Release\custprof.pdb"```

attributes.name: signatures
attributes.documentation: A zero-based array of signature objects, one for each authenticode signature in the PE file. Usually PE files have a single signature.

structure.name: signatures
structure.documentation: A zero-based array of signature objects, one for each authenticode signature in the PE file. Usually PE files have a single signature.

attributes.name: thumbprint
attributes.documentation: A string containing the thumbprint of the signature.

attributes.name: issuer
attributes.documentation: A string containing information about the issuer.

attributes.name: subject
attributes.documentation: A string containing information about the subject.

attributes.name: version
attributes.documentation: Version number.

attributes.name: algorithm
attributes.documentation: String representation of the algorithm used for this signature. Usually "sha1WithRSAEncryption". It depends on the X.509 and PKCS#7 implementationss and possibly their versions, consider using algorithm_oid instead.

attributes.name: algorithm_oid
attributes.documentation: Object ID of the algorithm used for this signature, expressed in numeric ASN.1 dot notation. The name contained in algorithm is derived from this value. The object id is expected to be stable across X.509 and PKCS#7 implementations and their versions.

attributes.name: serial
attributes.documentation: A string containing the serial number. This is an example: 52:00:e5:aa:25:56:fc:1a:86:ed:96:c9:d4:4b:33:c7

attributes.name: not_before
attributes.documentation: Unix timestamp on which the validity period for this signature begins.

attributes.name: not_after
attributes.documentation: Unix timestamp on which the validity period for this signature ends.

overloads.documentation: Function returning true if the signature was valid on the date indicated by timestamp. The following sentence: ```pe.signatures[n].valid_on(timestamp)``` Is equivalent to: ```timestamp >= pe.signatures[n].not_before and timestamp <= pe.signatures[n].not_after```

attributes.name: number_of_signatures
attributes.documentation: Number of authenticode signatures in the PE.

overloads.documentation: Function returning the file offset for RVA addr. Be careful to pass relative addresses here and not absolute addresses, like pe.entry_point when scanning a process. Example: ```pe.rva_to_offset(pe.sections[0].virtual_address) == pe.sections[0].raw_data_offset``` This example will make sure the offset for the virtual address in the first section equals the file offset for that section.
